@node Overview
@chapter Overview

@samp{copilot-extras.el} extends the @samp{copilot.el} package, which
integrates GitHub Copilot into Emacs.  The stock @samp{copilot-mode} is a
simple on/off toggle with no built-in awareness of buffer context.
This extension adds two pieces of missing functionality:

@itemize
@item
@strong{Conditional activation}: enable Copilot automatically in
programming buffers while skipping read-only buffers and
user-specified modes (@ref{Conditional activation}).
@item
@strong{Restart workaround}: quickly cycle @samp{copilot-mode} off and on when
the process stops responding (@ref{Restarting Copilot}).
@end itemize

