@node @code{copilot-extras-excluded-modes}
@section @code{copilot-extras-excluded-modes}

@vindex copilot-extras-excluded-modes
The user option @code{copilot-extras-excluded-modes} is a list of major
mode symbols in which @samp{copilot-mode} should @emph{not} be activated by
@code{copilot-extras-enable-conditionally}
(@ref{Conditional activation}).  You might add modes where inline
completions are distracting or conflict with other tools---for
example, terminal emulators, shell prompts, or documentation browsers.

The type is a list of symbols.  The default value is an empty list
@code{()}, meaning no modes are excluded beyond the read-only check.

