@node Conditional activation
@section Conditional activation

@findex copilot-extras-enable-conditionally
The function @code{copilot-extras-enable-conditionally} is designed to be
added to a hook such as @code{prog-mode-hook} or @code{text-mode-hook}.  It
activates @samp{copilot-mode} in the current buffer @emph{unless} either of the
following is true:

@enumerate
@item
The buffer is read-only (@code{buffer-read-only} is non-nil).
@item
The buffer's major mode appears in
@code{copilot-extras-excluded-modes} (@ref{@code{copilot-extras-excluded-modes}}).
@end enumerate

This provides a convenient ``enable everywhere except@dots{}'' policy without
requiring per-mode hook configuration.

@node Restarting Copilot
@section Restarting Copilot

@findex copilot-extras-restart-copilot
The function @code{copilot-extras-restart-copilot} quickly disables and
re-enables @samp{copilot-mode} in the current buffer, with a brief pause
between the two operations.  This is a workaround for situations where
the Copilot process stops providing suggestions.  The function only
acts when @samp{copilot-mode} is already active, so it is safe to call
unconditionally---for instance, from a periodic timer.

